{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e561e15b-7ef0-4ebd-928a-1df37da56518","content":"Yes, you **will** run into compatibility issues. MSTest v3 drops support for some of your target frameworks:\n\n| Target | Status in MSTest v3 |\n|---|---|\n| `net5.0` | ❌ **Dropped** — .NET 5 is not supported; minimum is .NET 6 (`net6.0`) |\n| `net462` | ❌ **Dropped** — .NET Framework older than 4.6.2 is the cutoff, but `net462` is exactly 4.6.2 so you should verify; typically you'd move to `net472` or later to be safe |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ **Dropped** — .NET Core 3.1 is not supported |\n\n**Before migrating**, you'll need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to supported versions. For example:\n\n- `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or `net8.0`)\n- `netcoreapp3.1` → remove or upgrade to `net6.0`+\n- `net462` → `net472` or later\n\nWould you like me to invoke the **MSTest v2→v3 migration skill** to walk through the full migration (including assertion API changes, `DataRow` constructor updates, timeout behavior changes, etc.)?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"af8290fb-5e07-4b6f-8ace-0c6c50ab89b4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project that targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They're using MSTest v2 (2.2.10). Let me invoke the MSTest migration skill to provide proper guidance.","outputTokens":386,"requestId":"6806:24EAAB:2FBC2AB:34F008B:69FD5067"},"id":"a687ee47-ffdb-4de2-b190-82d9485bdd9f","timestamp":"2026-05-08T02:54:39.146Z","parentId":"8de98775-8d6e-4c98-a842-5721a37ec3de"}
